# 15_polygon_spiral_popovers — substrate-layer suite for the
# Polygon and Spiral placement popovers' standalone widgets (s196 m2).
#
# Substrate-style test (per TESTING.md grandfather clause). Each
# sub-test proves the substrate contract holds — abbrev resolves,
# verbs dispatch, queries read back. SpinButtons exercise the
# set/value round-trip; Place buttons read their label.
#
# Scope (s196 m2): the standalone widgets in the Polygon and
# Spiral popovers — sides/inflect for polygon, turns/inner for
# spiral, plus both Place buttons. The position SpinButtons in
# these popovers (cx / cy / r) were migrated in s196 m1 as a side
# effect of the make_pop_row helper signature change; they're
# already covered by test 14.
#
# DSL note (from m1, repeated here for self-containment): the DSL
# lexer is kind-strict and assert uses no int/double coercion.
# SpinButton `value` queries return Double regardless of the
# `digits` constructor argument. Round-number literals must be
# written `5.0`, not `5`, or the assert fails with the misleading
# message `FAIL expected 5, got 5`.
#
# The tested abbrevs:
#
#   Polygon popover  pop_tb_pol_sd  (Sides — int range 3-64, digits 0)
#                    pop_tb_pol_in  (Inflect % — 1.0-100.0, digits 1)
#                    pop_tb_pol_pl  (Place Button)
#
#   Spiral popover   pop_tb_spi_tn  (Turns — 0.25-20.0, digits 2)
#                    pop_tb_spi_ir  (Inner r % — 0.0-95.0, digits 1)
#                    pop_tb_spi_pl  (Place Button)
#
# Test protocol:
#   1. Open the Scripter window.
#   2. Load this script.
#   3. Run. Every line should PASS.
#
# Side effects: SpinButton values are written to test set/value
# round-trip. Right-clicking the relevant tool re-seeds them from
# stored defaults on popup-open (poly_sides / poly_inflection /
# spiral_turns / spiral_inner are pulled into the spinners), so
# the residual values are harmless — they'll be overwritten the
# next time the user opens the popover. Place buttons are NOT
# clicked (would actually emit place signals and add nodes to the
# document). Label read-back is enough substrate-contract coverage
# for a Button.

#[sub] Polygon popover — Place button label.

assert pop_tb_pol_pl label == "Place"

#[sub] Polygon popover — sides SpinButton round-trip.

pop_tb_pol_sd set 5.0
assert pop_tb_pol_sd value == 5.0
pop_tb_pol_sd set 8.0
assert pop_tb_pol_sd value == 8.0

#[sub] Polygon popover — inflect SpinButton round-trip.

pop_tb_pol_in set 50.0
assert pop_tb_pol_in value == 50.0
pop_tb_pol_in set 75.5
assert pop_tb_pol_in value == 75.5

#[sub] Spiral popover — Place button label.

assert pop_tb_spi_pl label == "Place"

#[sub] Spiral popover — turns SpinButton round-trip.

pop_tb_spi_tn set 3.5
assert pop_tb_spi_tn value == 3.5
pop_tb_spi_tn set 7.25
assert pop_tb_spi_tn value == 7.25

#[sub] Spiral popover — inner r % SpinButton round-trip.

pop_tb_spi_ir set 25.0
assert pop_tb_spi_ir value == 25.0
pop_tb_spi_ir set 60.5
assert pop_tb_spi_ir value == 60.5

#[sub] Done. 6 new substrate widgets, all addressable.
